premise_source_doc_sentence: `` Longfellow Serenade '' is the title of a 1974 song by the American singer-songwriter Neil Diamond .
The title of the song is a reference to the 19th-century American poet Henry Wadsworth Longfellow .

Diamond described `` Longfellow Serenade '' in the liner notes to his 1996 compilation album , In My Lifetime : `` Occasionally I like using a particular lyrical style which , in this case , lent itself naturally to telling the story of a guy who woos his woman with poetry . ''
`` Longfellow Serenade '' spent two weeks at # 5 on the Billboard Hot 100 chart in November 1974 .
The CD release does not include the songs `` The Last Picasso '' and `` Longfellow Serenade '' .
